Is there VSCode full support ES7 async/await syntax?

I tried to use ES7 `async/await` syntax in VSCode. 
But i found that there was something wrong with my config, when i compiled the `*.tx` to `*.js`.

When I **compiled**, the error tips would **disappear**. But when I **modified** the file, the error tips  would **show again**.

Just liked this:

![issue](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1575657/12605008/a8c93ad8-c4fb-11e5-9e4b-dc01bfe5ad70.gif)

---

vscode: 0.10.6
tsc: 1.9.0-dev.20160126
node: 4.1.1

the code:

``` javascript
"use strict";

async function main() {
    await ping();
}

async function ping() {
    for (var i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
        await delay(300);
        console.log("ping");
    }

}

function delay(ms: number) {
    return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms));
}

main();
```

my config files:

tasks.json

``` json
{
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "command": "tsc",
    "isShellCommand": true,
    "showOutput": "silent",
    "args": ["-p", "."],
    "problemMatcher": "$tsc"
}
```

tsconfig.json

``` json
{
    "compilerOptions": {
        "target": "es2015",
        "module": "commonjs",
        "sourceMap": true,
        "outDir": "bin/",
        "moduleResolution": "classic"
    }
}
```

Have the following code:

```
/**
 * A person
 * @constructor
 * @param {string} name - The name of the person.
 * @param {number} age - The age of the person.
 */
function Person(name, age) {
    this.name = name;
    this.age = age;
}
```

Invoke the Person function and trigger paramter hints. Notice that there are two proposals for parameter hints, one for any, any and one for the specified jsdoc types. I would expect only the one for the specified types in the jsdoc. This way the user always has to press down to get to the correct value

